news.title: Delhi: Brick kiln industry protests over GST
news.para: Ashok Tewari, president of AIBTMF, said, “The GST council has proposed to hike tax from 5% to 12% with input tax credit (ITC) under the regular scheme and from 1% to 6% without ITC under the composition scheme."

news.title: Cabinet nod to SPV for monetisation of surplus land
news.para: The special purpose vehicle (SPV) called the National Land Monetisation Corporation (NLMC) will be set up as a wholly-owned Government of India company with an initial authorized share capital of Rs 5,000 crore and paid-up share capital of Rs 150 crore, an official statement said.

news.title: Stamp duty exemption for Mihan-SEZ expired last year
news.para: Sources related to the project said lack of stamp duty exemption can be a major setback for attracting investment here. Stamp duty comes as a major amount, especially for big land parcels.

news.title: Nagpur: 1,000 sq ft slum plot gets Rs 1.78 lakh demand for building plan sanction
news.para: This could become the norm, denying slum dwellers any chance to develop or regularise their properties, if the civic chief does not accept the general body’s decision to discard the proposed rules.

news.title: Sixteen new sectors to be developed off Yamuna Expressway
news.para: These new sectors will be included in the 2041 master plan of the Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA), which governs the region.

news.title: Naredco Nashik asks government to reduce GST on raw materials
news.para: Naredco has also alleged artificial rise in the cement and steel prices in the last few months, which has led to rise in construction cost. It has requested the government to take measures to ensure the prices remain stable for at least six months.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 16 commercial units for lack of BU permission
news.para: The department teams sealed 12 units in Block A of Falak Heights and four more units in Block B of the same society. The sealed units were operating without valid BU permissions.

news.title: Gurugram: 200 metre stretch blocked in Mayfield Garden for years, residents fume
news.para: The residents pointed out that there was a 14-metre-wide road abutting boundary wall of the women police station through a commercial site of 6 acres as per the approved layout plan of N block.

news.title: Deolali cantonment board teams to visit houses & ask people to pay tax
news.para: The Deolali Cantonment Board (DCB) has deployed different teams to make door-to-door visits to request people to pay property taxes as almost 18% recovery is pending even as the current financial year is drawing to a close.

news.title: Kalpataru group to invest Rs 250 crore to build housing project in Pune
news.para: The project, which is spread over 2.33 acres, comprises close to 450 apartments. The prices start at Rs 1.10 crore. "Close to a million square feet area will be developed at the project at an estimated cost of Rs 250 crore," the statement said.

news.title: Surat civic body seals 38 row houses doing commercial activities
news.para: The property owners have approached the court against SMC’s notice to discontinue commercial activity from residential properties.

news.title: 315Work Avenue lease out 800 seats to Square Yards in Pune
news.para: The company plans to add 5 lakh sq ft office space over a period of six months. "We have already witnessed a robust growth in this calendar year 2022 and have signed up around 3,000 seats in the last 1 month," said Manas Mehrotra, founder, 315Work Avenue.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board approves sale of properties on freehold
news.para: The board approved sale of vacant residential site measuring 4.95 acre in IT Park through e-tender process on freehold. The purchaser will be given required flexibilities in constructions and allowed to pay the whole bid amount in installments over a period of about five years.

news.title: No survey on air pollution by cement plants: Himachal Pradesh government
news.para: Government informed that no survey has been done to check the air pollution impact on the villages surrounding the cement plants. But the air quality is monitored by the state pollution control board.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Steel, cement prices up 35% in two months
news.para: While steel prices have touched Rs 80,500 per tonne, cement costs Rs 430 per bag, adding to the cost of construction in the ongoing projects.
